TITLE: Accessing Podman Machine via SSH (Windows/macOS)
DESCRIPTION: This command uses `podman machine ssh` to open a root shell session within the Podman virtual machine on Windows or macOS. This is necessary for accessing and modifying configuration files like `registries.conf` stored within the VM, particularly when configuring insecure registries. The `[optional-machine-name]` parameter can be used if managing multiple Podman machines.
SOURCE: https://github.com/podman-desktop/podman-desktop/blob/main/website/docs/containers/registries/index.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: shell-session
CODE:
```
$ podman machine ssh --username root [optional-machine-name]
```

