TITLE: Running a Virtual Machine with QEMU on macOS Silicon
DESCRIPTION: Commands to set up and run the generated raw bootable image on macOS Silicon using QEMU. This setup allocates 8GB of memory, 4 CPU cores, and forwards port 2222 to the VM's SSH port 22 for remote access.
SOURCE: https://github.com/podman-desktop/podman-desktop/blob/main/website/blog/2024-11-08-bootc-microshift.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: sh
CODE:
