TITLE: Attempting SSH into Podman Machine (libkrun Issue)
DESCRIPTION: This shell session output demonstrates the error received when trying to SSH into the default Podman machine (`podman machine ssh`) if that machine was created with the `libkrun` provider and the `CONTAINERS_MACHINE_PROVIDER` environment variable is not set to `libkrun`. The command fails because it cannot find the VM under the default provider (QEMU).
SOURCE: https://github.com/podman-desktop/podman-desktop/blob/main/website/docs/troubleshooting/troubleshooting-podman-on-macos.md#2025-04-23_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: shell-session
CODE:
```
$ podman machine ssh
Error: vm podman-machine-default not found: podman-machine-default: VM does not exist
```

